==Demographics==
At the [[2020 United States Census|2020 census]] there were 117 people, 39 households, and 27 families living in the CDP. The population density was 30 people per square mile. There were 68 housing units.

The median household income was $23,620. The per capita income for the CDP was $12,561.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://arizona.hometownlocator.com/az/pima/south-komelik.cfm |publisher=Arizona.hometownlocator.com |access-date=September 7, 2021 |date=2021 |title=South Komelik, AZ Profile: Facts & Data}}</ref>

